==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Red-dog flour
<hw>Red`-dog" flour</hw> }</mhw>.
<def>The lowest grade of flour in milling. It is dark and of little
expansive power, is secured largely from the germ or embryo and adjacent
parts, and contains a relatively high percentage of protein. It is
chiefly useful as feed for farm animals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reddour</ent>⟦br⟧
